-- China's Stocks Fluctuate After Fuel Price Increase; Oil Refiners Advance
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-22T02:14:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/china-s-stocks-fluctuate-after-fuel-price-increase-oil-refiners-advance.html
China’s stocks fluctuated as banks
declined on speculation higher risk weightings on lenders’ loans
will hurt earnings, overshadowing a rally for PetroChina Co. on
an increase in fuel prices.  The Shanghai Composite Index added 0.1 percent to 2,906 at
10:12 a.m., even as twice as many stocks fell than those that
advanced. The CSI 300 Index rose 0.2 percent to 3,255.42, led
by material and energy stocks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  